# 3. Every Phase Template

Every phase listed in Section 2 must be documented, at the time it becomes active, using exactly the following template. This ensures every phase's documentation is structurally identical regardless of which session writes it.

### Purpose
A one-paragraph statement of what the phase exists to accomplish and why it matters to the overall product.

### Scope
The specific, bounded set of functionality the phase will deliver — written narrowly enough that "is this in scope?" has an obvious answer for any given feature idea.

### Dependencies
Which prior phases (and which specific deliverables from them) this phase requires to already exist before it can begin.

### Deliverables
The concrete artifacts the phase will produce (e.g. specific pages, specific API modules per Phase 0.6, specific database tables per Phase 0.5) — described narratively, not as code.

### Completion Criteria
The specific, checkable conditions that must be true for the phase to be considered done — mirroring the Completion Criteria pattern already used in Phases 0.1–0.6.

### Out of Scope
An explicit list of adjacent functionality that is deliberately deferred to a later phase, to prevent scope creep during implementation.

Below is how this template applies to each phase at a roadmap level. Each phase's full, detailed spec is still written separately (per Phase 0.3's Documentation Standards) when that phase becomes active — the summaries below establish the boundaries that detailed spec must respect.

---

### Phase 1 — Project Initialization
- **Purpose:** Stand up the actual project codebase and static homepage matching the approved prototype.
- **Scope:** Repository/project setup using the locked stack (Phase 0.3), the folder structure (Phase 0.2), and a fully static homepage implementing the design system (Phase 0.4) — no auth, no live data, no backend calls.
- **Dependencies:** Phases 0.2, 0.3, 0.4.
- **Deliverables:** A running frontend application rendering the homepage pixel-faithful to the prototype, using placeholder/static data only.
- **Completion Criteria:** The homepage visually matches the prototype across desktop and the responsive rules in Phase 0.4; no functionality beyond static rendering exists yet.
- **Out of Scope:** Any real data, any backend, any authentication, any other page.

### Phase 2 — Authentication
- **Purpose:** Enable real user accounts.
- **Scope:** Sign up, log in, log out, and session handling via Supabase Auth (Phase 0.3), implementing the Authentication and Users API modules (Phase 0.6).
- **Dependencies:** Phase 1; Phase 0.5 (Users entity); Phase 0.6 (Authentication, Users modules).
- **Deliverables:** Working sign-up/login/logout flows; session-aware app shell (showing "Log in/Sign up" vs. an authenticated state).
- **Completion Criteria:** A user can create an account, log in, remain logged in across a session, and log out, with all rules from Phase 0.6's Authentication Rules enforced.
- **Out of Scope:** Profile editing, any feature beyond identity and session management.

### Phase 3 — Database Integration
- **Purpose:** Stand up the real, persistent data layer.
- **Scope:** Implementing the core entities from Phase 0.5 (Users, Profiles, Points Balance, Points Transactions at minimum) as actual Prisma models against PostgreSQL, per Phase 0.3.
- **Dependencies:** Phase 2; Phase 0.5 (full entity model); Phase 0.3 (Prisma/PostgreSQL).
- **Deliverables:** A working schema and data-access layer supporting the entities needed by subsequent phases.
- **Completion Criteria:** Core entities persist correctly, relationships match Phase 0.5 exactly, and deletion rules (soft/hard delete, per Phase 0.5 Section 6) are correctly implemented.
- **Out of Scope:** Market/Prediction-specific entities, which are introduced in their own phases as needed.

### Phase 4 — User Profiles
- **Purpose:** Give every user a public-facing identity.
- **Scope:** Profiles entity implementation and the Profiles API module (Phase 0.6); profile viewing and editing UI.
- **Dependencies:** Phases 2, 3.
- **Deliverables:** Public profile pages/components and an editable "my profile" experience.
- **Completion Criteria:** A user can view their own and others' public profiles, and edit their own, consistent with Phase 0.5's ownership rules.
- **Out of Scope:** Settings/preferences (Phase 16), Portfolio/Leaderboard integration (their own phases).

### Phase 5 — Categories
- **Purpose:** Support the category browsing structure shown in the sidebar.
- **Scope:** Categories entity, Categories API module, and category display in the sidebar/UI.
- **Dependencies:** Phase 3.
- **Deliverables:** A real, database-backed category list replacing the Phase 1 static placeholder, matching Phase 0.4's sidebar design exactly.
- **Completion Criteria:** Categories display correctly with real active/"Soon" status and accurate market counts (initially zero until Phase 6).
- **Out of Scope:** Market data itself.

### Phase 6 — Markets
- **Purpose:** Introduce real, browsable markets.
- **Scope:** Markets and Market Options entities; Markets API module; Markets browsing/search/filter UI.
- **Dependencies:** Phases 3, 5.
- **Deliverables:** A real Markets listing and browsing experience replacing Phase 1's static Trending Markets placeholder.
- **Completion Criteria:** Markets can be listed, filtered by category, searched, and sorted, consistent with Phase 0.6's Markets module contract.
- **Out of Scope:** Placing predictions, market detail pages (Phase 7), admin market creation (Phase 17, though basic seeding may be needed earlier as a documented exception).

### Phase 7 — Market Details
- **Purpose:** Give each market a dedicated detail view.
- **Scope:** Market Detail page/UI and any additional API needs beyond the base Markets module.
- **Dependencies:** Phase 6.
- **Deliverables:** A market detail page showing full market information, ready to host prediction placement in Phase 8.
- **Completion Criteria:** A user can navigate from a market row to a full detail view showing all relevant market data.
- **Out of Scope:** Actual prediction placement logic.

### Phase 8 — Prediction Engine
- **Purpose:** Enable the platform's core action — placing predictions with Points.
- **Scope:** Predictions and Prediction History entities; Predictions API module; prediction placement UI on the Market Detail page; market lifecycle/settlement logic (per Phase 0.5 Section 8).
- **Dependencies:** Phases 3, 7; Phase 11 (Points System) must be sequenced carefully — see Dependency Note below.
- **Deliverables:** Working end-to-end prediction placement, locking, and settlement flow.
- **Completion Criteria:** A user can place a prediction, see it locked when its market closes, and see it resolve correctly at settlement, with all Points movements correctly ledgered.
- **Out of Scope:** Portfolio aggregation UI (Phase 9), Leaderboard impact (Phase 10).
- **Dependency Note:** Because Predictions inherently require Points movement, a minimal Points ledger capability must exist by this phase even though the full Points System phase is numbered later; this is resolved by implementing the foundational Points Transactions/Balance data layer as part of Phase 3, with Phase 11 building the complete user-facing Points experience on top of it.

### Phase 9 — Portfolio
- **Purpose:** Give users a summary view of their current standing.
- **Scope:** Portfolio and Portfolio History entities; Portfolio API module; Portfolio UI.
- **Dependencies:** Phase 8.
- **Deliverables:** A working Portfolio page showing current holdings and historical trend.
- **Completion Criteria:** Portfolio accurately reflects a user's active predictions and historical snapshots, consistent with Phase 0.5's derived-data philosophy.
- **Out of Scope:** Leaderboard ranking logic.

### Phase 10 — Leaderboards
- **Purpose:** Rank users by performance.
- **Scope:** Leaderboard entity; Leaderboard API module; Leaderboard UI.
- **Dependencies:** Phases 8, 9.
- **Deliverables:** A working, periodically-refreshed leaderboard.
- **Completion Criteria:** Leaderboard displays accurate rankings computed from Prediction History and Points Transactions, per Phase 0.5's computed-projection philosophy.
- **Out of Scope:** Achievement-based recognitions (Phase 12).

### Phase 11 — Points System
- **Purpose:** Complete the full user-facing Points experience.
- **Scope:** Full Points and Points Transactions API modules; Points display throughout the UI (navbar, Portfolio); Points history view.
- **Dependencies:** Phase 3's foundational ledger (per Phase 8's Dependency Note).
- **Deliverables:** A complete, transparent Points experience, including a user-facing transaction history view.
- **Completion Criteria:** Every Points movement anywhere in the product is visible and traceable to the user through this system.
- **Out of Scope:** Reward-specific claiming logic (Phase 12).

### Phase 12 — Rewards & Achievements
- **Purpose:** Deliver the XP/perks program teased in the prototype.
- **Scope:** Rewards and Achievements entities; Rewards/Achievements API modules; Rewards UI.
- **Dependencies:** Phase 11.
- **Deliverables:** A working Rewards Program experience, including achievement tracking and reward claiming.
- **Completion Criteria:** Users can view available rewards/achievements, track progress, and claim eligible rewards, with all resulting Points movements correctly ledgered.
- **Out of Scope:** Admin-side reward definition management (Phase 17, though basic seeding may be required earlier as a documented exception).

### Phase 13 — Activity Feed
- **Purpose:** Surface a live, global feed of platform activity.
- **Scope:** Activity Feed entity; Activity Feed API module; Recent Activity UI, replacing Phase 1's static placeholder.
- **Dependencies:** Phase 8 (predictions as a primary activity source).
- **Deliverables:** A real, live-updating Activity Feed.
- **Completion Criteria:** Activity Feed accurately reflects real platform events in chronological order, matching Phase 0.4's design.
- **Out of Scope:** Per-user Notifications (Phase 14).

### Phase 14 — Notifications
- **Purpose:** Deliver targeted, per-user alerts.
- **Scope:** Notifications entity; Notifications API module; Notifications UI.
- **Dependencies:** Phase 13.
- **Deliverables:** A working notifications experience with read/unread state.
- **Completion Criteria:** Users receive notifications for relevant events (e.g. a prediction resolving) and can manage read state.
- **Out of Scope:** Notification preference configuration (Phase 16).

### Phase 15 — Search
- **Purpose:** Make the platform's content findable.
- **Scope:** Full implementation of the search bar shown in the prototype, backed by the search philosophy in Phase 0.6.
- **Dependencies:** Phase 6.
- **Deliverables:** A working, performant search experience across Markets (and any other searchable content identified at this phase).
- **Completion Criteria:** Search returns accurate, relevant results with acceptable performance at the scale anticipated in Phase 0.5.
- **Out of Scope:** Search-driven recommendations or discovery algorithms beyond direct query matching.

### Phase 16 — Settings
- **Purpose:** Give users control over their account configuration.
- **Scope:** User Settings entity; User Settings API module; Settings UI, including notification preferences.
- **Dependencies:** Phases 4, 14.
- **Deliverables:** A working account settings experience.
- **Completion Criteria:** Users can view and update their settings, and those settings correctly affect platform behavior (e.g. notification delivery).
- **Out of Scope:** Admin-level configuration (System Configuration, Phase 17).

### Phase 17 — Admin Panel
- **Purpose:** Give the project owner (as Admin) tools to manage the platform.
- **Scope:** Admin Users, Admin Actions, System Configuration, and Audit Logs entities; the full Admin API module; an Admin UI covering Market/Category/Reward management and audit log review, per Phase 0.6 Section 12.
- **Dependencies:** Phases 6, 12; core data layer from Phase 3.
- **Deliverables:** A working Admin Panel sufficient to operate the platform without direct database access.
- **Completion Criteria:** All administrative operations identified in Phase 0.6 are available, authorized, and logged correctly.
- **Out of Scope:** Advanced permission granularity beyond what Phase 0.6 anticipates (deferred to a future, explicitly scoped enhancement).

### Phase 18 — Performance Optimization
- **Purpose:** Ensure the platform performs well under real usage.
- **Scope:** Applying the caching, pagination, indexing, and bundle-optimization philosophies from Phases 0.3 and 0.6 in practice, across the now-complete feature set.
- **Dependencies:** All preceding functional phases (1–17).
- **Deliverables:** Measured performance improvements across frontend load time, API response time, and database query performance.
- **Completion Criteria:** Defined performance benchmarks (established at the start of this phase) are met across key user flows (homepage load, market browsing, prediction placement).
- **Out of Scope:** New features of any kind.

### Phase 19 — Security Hardening
- **Purpose:** Verify and strengthen the platform's security posture before launch.
- **Scope:** A full review against the Security Standards in Phases 0.3 and 0.6 — authentication, authorization, input sanitization, rate limiting, secrets handling.
- **Dependencies:** All preceding functional phases.
- **Deliverables:** A documented security review and remediation of any findings.
- **Completion Criteria:** No known high-severity security gaps remain against the standards already locked in this project's documentation.
- **Out of Scope:** New features of any kind.

### Phase 20 — Testing
- **Purpose:** Establish confidence in the platform's correctness before launch.
- **Scope:** Applying the Testing Strategy defined in Section 7 of this document across all implemented functionality.
- **Dependencies:** All preceding functional phases.
- **Deliverables:** A test suite covering critical paths (authentication, prediction placement/settlement, Points integrity) and a documented manual testing pass.
- **Completion Criteria:** Critical paths are covered by automated tests, and a full manual regression pass finds no blocking issues.
- **Out of Scope:** New features of any kind.

### Phase 21 — Deployment
- **Purpose:** Stand up the real, production infrastructure.
- **Scope:** Implementing the Deployment Roadmap in Section 8 — environment separation, staging, and production deployment using Vercel, Railway, Supabase, and Cloudflare, per Phase 0.3.
- **Dependencies:** Phases 18, 19, 20.
- **Deliverables:** A fully deployed staging environment, validated, followed by a production environment.
- **Completion Criteria:** The platform runs correctly in a production-equivalent environment with the custom domain and DNS configured, per Phase 0.3.
- **Out of Scope:** The public launch itself (Phase 22).

### Phase 22 — Production Launch
- **Purpose:** Officially launch the platform.
- **Scope:** Final pre-launch checks against the Success Criteria in Section 12, and the actual go-live.
- **Dependencies:** Phase 21.
- **Deliverables:** A live, publicly accessible production platform.
- **Completion Criteria:** All Success Criteria in Section 12 are met.
- **Out of Scope:** Post-launch feature development, which proceeds under the Maintenance Philosophy in Section 10.

