# 14. Completion Criteria

Phase 0.7 is considered complete when:

1. This document exists at `docs/Phase-0.7-Development-Roadmap-and-Implementation-Plan.md` and is committed with a `docs:` commit, per Phase 0.3's Git Standards.
2. Every phase from 1 through 22 is listed in the roadmap (Section 2) and summarized using the template from Section 3, with clear dependencies on prior phases and this project's existing documentation (Phases 0.2–0.6).
3. Development, Git, quality, testing, deployment, release, and maintenance practices (Sections 4–10) are fully defined with no open questions.
4. Risks (Section 11) and Success Criteria (Section 12) are explicitly documented.
5. The document contains no application code, schema, or implementation of any kind.
6. The document has been reviewed and explicitly approved by the project owner as the permanent execution roadmap for the rest of the project.

Once these conditions are met, Phase 0.7 is closed, and the foundational documentation set (Phases 0.1–0.7) is complete. Phase 1 (Project Initialization) may then begin, implementing the static homepage using the technology stack (Phase 0.3) and design system (Phase 0.4) already locked.

